<L>__{interior holiday inn holidome, hallway moments later}
<A>__{cell phone to his ear, tim struggles with his bag as he walks to his room.}
<C>__{millie }
<D>__{have you seen the pool yet?}
<C>__{tim}
<D>__{not yet, but i can smell it. the chlorine. it's a super top notch place, mil. you'd be blown away. oop, 321. i'm at mi casa. just a... lemme see how this deal works.}
<A>__{he examines the card key. he slides it in. it doesn't work. tries again. doesn't work. each time he fails, it beeps.}
<C>__{tim }
<D>__{key's like a stinkin' credit card.}
<A>__{suddenly, the door opens. and standing before tim is a black man. tim gasps, drops his suitcase, backs away.}
<C>__{millie }
<D>__{what? what happened?}
<C>__{tim}
<P>__{(to the man)}
<D>__{oh jeez. i'm sorry. i'm... please.}
<P>__{(turns, whispers into phone)}
<D>__{there's an afro american gentleman in this room.}
<C>__{millie }
<D>__{well get the heck outta there!}
<A>__{tim turns back and smiles, frightened. the man looks confused.}
<D>__{millie (o.s. on phone) (cont'd) tim! run like hell, tim!}
